@startuml rats-zeta-tpm-attestation
' ============================================================
' RATS Remote Attestation (RFC 9334) integrated into ZETA
' Roles:
'   Attester        = ZETA Attestation Service (ZAS)
'   Verifier        = ZETA Guard AuthS (PDP Authorization Server)
'   Relying Party   = ZETA Guard AuthS (PDP Authorization Server)
'   Endorser        = OPA Policy Engine (PAP/PIP)
'   ZETA Client     = Intermediary between ZAS and AuthS
' ============================================================

!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #666
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F8F8F8
skinparam noteBorderColor #999
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
skinparam participantBorderColor #1565C0
skinparam lifelineBorderColor #90A4AE

title RATS TPM Attestation in ZETA (RFC 9334)\nAttester=ZAS | Verifier/RP=AuthS | Endorser=OPA

' ============================================================
' Participants
' ============================================================

box "Primärsystem / Client Environment" #EDE7F6
    participant TPM as tpm #D1C4E9
    participant "ZETA Attestation\nService (ZAS)\n[Attester]" as zas #B39DDB
    participant "ZETA Client\n[Initiator]" as client #9575CD
end box

box "ZETA Guard" #E8F5E9
    participant "AuthS\n[Verifier + Relying Party]" as auths #66BB6A
    participant "OPA Policy Engine\n[Endorser]" as opa #43A047
end box

box "TPM Manufacturer" #FFF3E0
    participant "Hersteller CA\n[EK Trust Anchor]" as mfr #FFA726
end box

' ============================================================
' Phase 0: Boot / Primärsystem-Start (Attester-seitig)
' ============================================================

== Phase 0: Primärsystem-Start — Integrity Measurement (RFC 9334: §4 Attesting Environment) ==

note over tpm
  TPM initialisiert:
  PCR 0–7: BIOS/UEFI
  PCR 8–15: Boot Chain
  PCR 23: Application-spezifisch
end note

tpm -> tpm : PCR 0–15 werden durch\nBoot-Prozess befüllt\n(BIOS, Bootloader, OS)

zas -> tpm : TPM2_HashSequenceStart /\nTPM2_SequenceUpdate\n(Primärsystem-Dateien messen)
tpm -> tpm : **PCR 23 Extend**\n(Hash der Primärsystem-Komponenten)
tpm --> zas : PCR 23 Extend Confirmation

note right of zas #FFFDE7
  **RATS: Evidence Generation (RFC 9334 §3.3)**
  ZAS erzeugt im Hintergrund:
  - AK (Attestation Key, TPM-resident)
  - EK liegt fest im TPM (Hersteller)
  ZAS ist bereit für Attestation-Requests
end note

' ============================================================
' Phase 1: DCR — EK und AK beim AuthS registrieren
' ============================================================

== Phase 1: OAuth Dynamic Client Registration (DCR) — EK & AK Registrierung ==

note over client, auths #E3F2FD
  **RATS: Endorsement Provisioning (RFC 9334 §3.2)**
  EK-Zertifikat = vom Hersteller signiertes Endorsement → Vertrauensanker
  AK-PublicKey  = wird im MakeCredential-Protokoll an EK gebunden
end note

client -> zas : Anfrage: EK-Zertifikat, AK-PublicKey
zas -> tpm : TPM2_ReadPublic(EK)\nTPM2_ReadPublic(AK)
tpm --> zas : EK_PublicKey, AK_PublicKey
zas --> client : ek_certificate_chain[ ]\n(Blatt bis Root)\nak_public_key (PEM)

client -> auths : **POST /register (DCR)**\n{\n  software_statement (JWT, SM(C)-B signiert),\n  client_instance_key (DPoP/Assertion Key),\n  ek_certificate (Blatt),\n  ek_certificate_chain[ ],\n  ak_public_key\n}

auths -> mfr : EK-Zertifikatskette validieren\n(OCSP / CRL)
mfr --> auths : Validation OK ✓

note right of auths #FFFDE7
  **RATS: Verifier prüft Endorsement (RFC 9334 §3.4)**
  AuthS führt MakeCredential aus:
  credentialBlob = Encrypt(
    EK_PublicKey,
    nonce,
    Hash(AK_PublicKey)  ← AK-Name
  )
end note

auths -> auths : **MakeCredential**\n(EK_PubKey, nonce, AK-Name)\n→ credentialBlob, encryptedSecret

auths --> client : {\n  credentialBlob,\n  encryptedSecret\n}

client -> zas : credentialBlob, encryptedSecret
zas -> tpm : **TPM2_ActivateCredential**\n(credentialBlob, encryptedSecret)
note right of tpm #FFFDE7
  TPM prüft intern:
  1. EK-PrivKey entschlüsselt Secret
  2. AK-Name muss übereinstimmen
  Nur wenn BEIDE im selben TPM → Secret freigegeben
end note
tpm --> zas : secret (nonce)
zas --> client : secret

client -> auths : **POST /register (Bestätigung)**\n{ secret }

auths -> auths : secret == gespeicherte nonce?\n→ **AK ist TPM-gebunden ✓**\nclient_id ↔ AK ↔ EK registriert

auths --> client : **201 Created**\n{ client_id }

note over auths #E8F5E9
  AuthS speichert dauerhaft:
  client_id ↔ client_instance_key ↔ ak_public_key ↔ ek_certificate
  EK-Chain wird **nicht** bei jedem Request erneut übermittelt
end note

' ============================================================
' Phase 2: Token-Anfrage mit TPM-Attestation
' ============================================================

== Phase 2: Token Exchange mit TPM Remote Attestation (RFC 9334: Passport Model) ==

note over client, auths #E3F2FD
  **RATS Passport Model (RFC 9334 §5.1)**
  1. Client holt Attestation Result vom Verifier (AuthS)
  2. AuthS als Relying Party nutzt sein eigenes Attestation Result
  (Verifier == Relying Party in ZETA)
end note

client -> auths : **POST /nonce**\n{ client_id }
auths --> client : nonce (Freshness, Replay-Schutz)

client -> zas : **gRPC: AttestationRequest**\n{ nonce, pcr_selection }

note right of zas
  ZAS fordert TPM Quote an
  mit der Nonce des AuthS
end note

zas -> tpm : **TPM2_Quote**\n(pcr_selection=[0..7, 23], nonce)
tpm --> zas : tpm_quote\n(PCR-Werte + nonce, signiert mit AK-PrivKey)
zas -> tpm : TPM2_GetEventLog()
tpm --> zas : tpm_event_log

note right of zas #FFFDE7
  **RATS: Evidence (RFC 9334 §3.3)**
  Evidence enthält:
  - tpm_quote: PCR-Snapshot + Nonce, AK-signiert
  - tpm_event_log: Replay-Grundlage
  - ak_public_key: zur Signaturverifikation
  - Posture-Daten (OS, Version, Arch, ...)
end note

zas --> client : **AttestationResponse**\n{\n  ak_public_key,\n  tpm_quote,\n  tpm_event_log,\n  posture (os, os_version, arch,\n           product_id, product_version)\n}

client -> auths : **POST /token** (RFC 8693 Token Exchange)\n{\n  grant_type: urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange,\n  client_assertion (JWT, signiert mit client_instance_key),\n  dpop_proof,\n  subject_token (SMC-B / GesundheitsID),\n  ak_public_key,\n  tpm_quote,\n  tpm_event_log,\n  posture\n}

' ============================================================
' Phase 3: Verifikation im AuthS (Verifier-Logik)
' ============================================================

== Phase 3: Attestation Verification im AuthS (RFC 9334 §3.4 Verifier) ==

auths -> auths : 1. client_assertion verifizieren\n   (client_instance_key aus DCR)

auths -> auths : 2. ak_public_key == registrierter AK?\n   (aus DCR gebunden)

auths -> auths : 3. **tpm_quote verifizieren**\n   - Signatur mit AK_PublicKey prüfen\n   - Nonce in Quote == gesendete Nonce?

auths -> auths : 4. **Event Log Replay**\n   PCR-Werte in Quote ==\n   Hash-Replay über tpm_event_log?

auths -> auths : 5. Posture-Daten extrahieren\n   (PCR 23, OS-Version, Product-ID, ...)

note right of auths #FFFDE7
  **RATS: Appraisal Policy Application (RFC 9334 §3.4)**
  AuthS hat rohe Evidence geprüft.
  Jetzt: Attestation Result erzeugen
  via OPA Policy Engine (Endorser)
end note

auths -> opa : **OPA Policy Query**\n{\n  pcr_values: { pcr23: "...", ... },\n  posture: { os_version, product_version, ... },\n  client_id,\n  ak_bound: true\n}

note right of opa #FFFDE7
  **RATS: Endorser (RFC 9334 §3.2)**
  OPA prüft gegen:
  - Referenzwerte für PCR 23\n    (gemeldete Hashes des Herstellers)
  - Erlaubte OS-Versionen
  - Erlaubte Produktversionen
  - Policy: client_id zugelassen?
end note

opa -> opa : Referenzwerte laden\n(PIP/PAP Repository)
opa --> auths : **Policy Decision**\n{\n  attestation_result: "pass" | "fail",\n  trust_level: "affirming" | "warning" | "contraindicated",\n  claims: { pcr23_valid, os_ok, version_ok }\n}

alt Attestation Result: pass
    auths -> auths : **Attestation Result = PASS**\n(RFC 9334: affirming)
    auths --> client : **200 OK**\n{\n  access_token (JWT),\n  token_type: "DPoP",\n  expires_in,\n  attestation_result: "affirming"\n}
else Attestation Result: fail
    auths --> client : **403 Forbidden**\n{\n  error: "access_denied",\n  error_description: "attestation_failed",\n  attestation_result: "contraindicated"\n}
end

' ============================================================
' Phase 4: Resource Access
' ============================================================

== Phase 4: Resource Access (Relying Party konsumiert Attestation Result) ==

note over client, auths #E3F2FD
  **RATS: Relying Party (RFC 9334 §3.5)**
  AuthS ist gleichzeitig Relying Party:
  Das Attestation Result ist bereits im Access Token eingebettet.
  Der PEP (HTTP Proxy) prüft das Token und gewährt Zugriff.
end note

client -> auths : **HTTP Request + Authorization: DPoP <access_token>**\n(via PEP HTTP Proxy)
auths -> auths : Token validieren\n(Signatur, Expiry,\nAttestation Result im Token)
auths --> client : **200 OK — Resource Access granted**

' ============================================================
' Legend
' ============================================================

legend right
  **RATS RFC 9334 Rollenverteilung in ZETA**
  |= RFC 9334 Rolle      |= ZETA Komponente               |
  | Attesting Environment | TPM (Hardware)                 |
  | Attester              | ZETA Attestation Service (ZAS) |
  | Verifier              | ZETA Guard AuthS               |
  | Relying Party         | ZETA Guard AuthS               |
  | Endorser              | OPA Policy Engine (PAP/PIP)    |
  | Conveyance            | ZETA Client (Intermediary)     |

  **RATS Modell:** Passport Model (RFC 9334 §5.1)
  **AK-Bindung:** MakeCredential / ActivateCredential (TPM 2.0)
  **EK-Registrierung:** einmalig bei DCR (kein Overhead pro Request)
endlegend

@enduml
